
- logging to file
see: 
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/17366579/celery-logs-into-file
https://docs.celeryq.dev/en/latest/userguide/tasks.html#logging

    $ celery worker 
        -A <module>:<appname>
        --loglevel <level> | -l <level>
        --logfile <file> | -f <file>

    e.g.
    
    $ celery worker -A celery_app:celery --loglevel debug --logfile ~/tmp/logs/celery.log
